&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goa has been chosen to host the FIDE World Cup 2025, bringing the global chess tournament back to India after 23 years.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;The World Cup will take place from October 31 to November 27, 2025, in North Goa, attracting 206 elite players from 82 countries.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The event will feature a prize purse of USD 2 million (approx. INR 17.58 crore), adding a competitive edge to the knockout tournament.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The logo of the event reflects Goa&amp;rsquo;s cultural identity with vibrant representations of its coastal beauty, chess, and festive spirit.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The anthem, &amp;ldquo;It&amp;rsquo;s Your Move&amp;rdquo;, voiced by Daler Mehndi, showcases India&amp;#39;s growing influence in global chess, featuring Prime Minister Narendra Modi and top Indian chess stars.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a significant step in India&amp;rsquo;s journey to becoming a global sports destination and further solidifies its position in world chess.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goa as Host&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The state is set to showcase its vibrant culture, strategic location, and world-class facilities as a sports destination.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Goa&amp;rsquo;s coastal beauty and festive atmosphere are symbolized in the tournament&amp;#39;s logo.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FIDE World Cup 2025 Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The tournament will feature a knockout format, attracting top chess players worldwide.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The event signifies India&amp;rsquo;s increasing prominence as a global chess hub and sports destination.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role of Chess in India&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;India&amp;#39;s growing involvement in chess is reflected through young grandmasters and increasing public interest in the sport.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The event will further boost India&amp;rsquo;s reputation in international sports and highlight its cultural legacy in the global sporting community.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A mountain range is a group or chain of mountains that are near together and formed by orogenic forces.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Aravalli Range&lt;/strong&gt; (sometimes called Aravali) is a mountain range in &lt;strong&gt;Northern-Western&lt;/strong&gt; India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It runs roughly &lt;u&gt;670 kilometers (430 miles)&lt;/u&gt; from &lt;strong&gt;Delhi&lt;/strong&gt; to &lt;strong&gt;Gujarat&lt;/strong&gt;, going through &lt;u&gt;southern Haryana and Rajasthan.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Guru Shikhar&lt;/strong&gt;, at &lt;strong&gt;1,722 meters&lt;/strong&gt;, is the t&lt;u&gt;allest summit (5,650 ft).&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Aravalli Range, which dates back to the &lt;strong&gt;Proterozoic era&lt;/strong&gt;, is considered the &lt;u&gt;world&amp;#39;s oldest fold mountain system.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vindhya&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Satpura&lt;/strong&gt; ranges run &lt;u&gt;parallel to each othe&lt;/u&gt;r and separate peninsular India from the mainland.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Himalayas &lt;/strong&gt;protect the Indian subcontinent from the &lt;strong&gt;North East &lt;/strong&gt;as a &lt;u&gt;natural barrier&lt;/u&gt; providing&lt;u&gt; geopolitical benefits &lt;/u&gt;to the country.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Vindhya, Satpura are block mountains.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Himalayas&lt;/u&gt; is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;young-fold mountain.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Hence, Aravallis is the oldest folded mountain in India.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
